'''Chatswood''' is a [[suburb]] in the city of [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]]. It contains a primary school and many parks. To the south of Chatswood is Kendall's Bay, a small bay of the Waitemata Harbour. The suburb is in the North Shore ward, one of the thirteen administrative divisions of Auckland City.
The population was 3,834 in the [[New Zealand Census of Population and Dwellings|2006 Census]], an increase of 147 from 2001.<ref>The statistical area used by the Census is called Chelsea. {{NZ Quickstats|3510402|Chelsea}}</ref>
==Education== Chelsea School is a coeducational contributing primary (years 1-6) school with a [[Socio-Economic Decile|decile rating]] of 10 and a roll of 355.<ref>{{TKI|1244|Chelsea School}}</ref> It was built in 1981.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chelsea.school.nz/aboutus.html|title= About Chelsea School|publisher=Chelsea School|accessdate=2009-01-12}}</ref>
